l lines, Orgad and Gill explore alternative articulations of feminism that go beyond the confidence imperative.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aGill, Rosalind, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107669120 cprintz978147801760840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478021834?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021834423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021834/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles